Notification Microservice:

Overview:

The Notification Microservice is a backend system designed to handle sending notifications across multiple channels like Email and SMS in a scalable and reliable way.
In real-world applications (e-commerce, banking, SaaS), sending notifications is a critical but complex problem — you need retries, fault tolerance, and asynchronous processing to avoid losing messages. This project focuses on solving exactly that.

Key Highlights:
Fully asynchronous, event-driven architecture using Kafka
Fault-tolerant processing with retry and dead letter queue (DLQ)
Multi-threaded worker system for high throughput
Template-based notifications using Thymeleaf

Architecture & Design:
This service follows an event-driven, asynchronous design where notification requests are first published to Kafka and then processed reliably in the background.

Instead of sending notifications immediately, events are:
Persisted before acknowledgment to avoid data loss
Pulled in batches by a scheduler for controlled processing
Executed in parallel using a thread pool for higher throughput
A dedicated processor resolves templates and dynamically routes notifications to the appropriate channel (Email/SMS), keeping the system extensible and clean.

To ensure reliability:
Failed notifications are retried multiple times
Persistent failures are moved to a Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)


Flow Diagram:

[Producer Service] → Kafka Topic (notification.event) → [Notification Consumer] → [PostgreSQL] 
                                                                                         │
                                                                                         ▼
                                                                               [Scheduled Worker]
                                                                                         │
                                                                                         ▼
                                                                              [Thread Pool Executor]
                                                                                   │     │     │
                                                                                   ▼     ▼     ▼
                                                                              [Notification Processor]
                                                                                       │
                                                                                       ▼
                                                                                   [Channel Router]
                                                                              ┌─────────┼─────────┐
                                                                              ▼         ▼         ▼
                                                                           [Email]    [SMS]   [Extensible]
	                                                                           │        │        │
	                                                                           ▼        ▼        ▼
                                                                                 Retry → DLQ



Tech Stack:
Backend: Spring Boot (Java)
Database: PostgreSQL
Messaging: Apache Kafka
Template Engine: Thymeleaf
Email: SMTP
SMS: Mock implementation
Build Tool: Maven
Containerization: Docker



Features:
Asynchronous notification processing
Multi-channel support (Email, SMS — extensible)
Retry mechanism for failed notifications
Dead Letter Queue (DLQ) for permanent failures
Template-based notification generation
Batch processing using scheduler
Multi-threaded execution for parallel processing
Status tracking (PENDING, SENT, FAILED)